# Zewail Campus Digital Assistant — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your key:
#
#   copy .env.example .env    (Windows)
#   cp .env.example .env      (Linux/Mac)
#
# Product A (RAG chat) requires ONE of the keys below.
# Product B (XAI dashboard) is fully local — no API key needed.

# ── Option 1: Standard OpenAI key (https://platform.openai.com/api-keys) ──────
# Best quality. Embeddings + GPT-4o chat both covered by this key.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...your-openai-key-here...

# ── Option 2: Groq key — FREE, no credit card (https://console.groq.com) ──────
# Sign up → API Keys → Create key. Free tier: 14 400 req/day.
# Chat uses LLaMA 3.3 70B (strong, fast). Embeddings fall back to keyword search
# over the stored ChromaDB documents — no rebuild needed.
OPENAI_API_KEY=gsk_...your-groq-key-here...

# ── Option 3: OpenRouter key (https://openrouter.ai/keys) ─────────────────────
# Cheap pay-as-you-go alternative to OpenAI. Auto-detected by sk-or-v1- prefix.
# Chat routes through OpenRouter. Add OPENAI_EMBED_KEY below for full semantic search.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-...your-openrouter-key-here...

# ── Optional: separate embedding key (OpenRouter or Groq users only) ──────────
# If set, semantic vector search is used instead of keyword fallback.
# Leave blank if you don't have one — keyword search works fine for most queries.
# OPENAI_EMBED_KEY=sk-...your-openai-embed-key-here...
